The Minister of Tourism, Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane will meet with the tourism industry on Monday, 09 March 2020, in light of the latest development around COVID-19. JOHANNESBURG - The Minister of Tourism Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane will meet with the tourism industry on Monday evening in light of the latest development around COVID-19. The coronavirus outbreak could severely impact the tourism industry. WATCH: Inter-ministerial committee holds COVID-19 briefing With at least seven cases of Covid-19 confirmed in South Africa so far, some of the world's most famous sites have been shut, knocking tourist numbers. Tourism is one of the biggest contributors to the economy.